## Technical Approach

### Library Choice: jsPDF

**Why jsPDF:**
- Most popular PDF library (29k stars)
- 8-10KB gzipped (acceptable)
- Supports text, headings, lists, tables
- Active maintenance (last update 2024)
- No backend needed (client-side only)

**Alternatives considered:**
- html2pdf.js: Larger (15KB), slower
- pdfmake: Complex API, steeper learning curve
- Browser print: Poor quality, no control

### Implementation Strategy

**Step 1: Install jsPDF**
```bash
npm install jspdf
```

**Step 2: Convert Lexical State to PDF**

Lexical editor stores content as JSON tree. We need to traverse it and convert to PDF.

**Example Lexical state:**
```json
{
  "root": {
    "children": [
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "tag": "h1",
        "children": [{ "text": "My Note Title" }]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "children": [{ "text": "Some content..." }]
      },
      {
        "type": "list",
        "listType": "bullet",
        "children": [
          { "text": "Item 1" },
          { "text": "Item 2" }
        ]
      }
    ]
  }
}
```

**PDF conversion:**
```typescript
import jsPDF from 'jspdf';

function exportNoteToPDF(note: Note) {
  const doc = new jsPDF();

  // Parse Lexical JSON state
  const editorState = JSON.parse(note.content);

  // Traverse nodes and add to PDF
  let yPosition = 20; // Start position

  editorState.root.children.forEach((node) => {
    if (node.type === 'heading') {
      doc.setFontSize(node.tag === 'h1' ? 20 : 16);
      doc.text(node.children[0].text, 20, yPosition);
      yPosition += 15;
    } else if (node.type === 'paragraph') {
      doc.setFontSize(12);
      doc.text(node.children[0].text, 20, yPosition);
      yPosition += 10;
    }
    // ... handle lists, tables, etc.
  });

  // Save PDF
  doc.save(`${note.title}-${formatDate(new Date())}.pdf`);
}
```

**Step 3: Add Export Button to Notes UI**

Add button to Notes page toolbar (next to other actions):
```typescript
<button onClick={() => exportNoteToPDF(activeNote)}>
  📄 Export PDF
</button>
```

