### Technical Decisions

1. **Use contentText instead of parsing Lexical JSON**: Simpler MVP approach, avoids complex node traversal
2. **Lazy load jsPDF**: Critical decision to prevent bundle bloat - jsPDF only loads when user clicks export
3. **A4 format with auto pagination**: Standard PDF size, handles long notes gracefully
4. **Filename sanitization**: Remove special characters, limit to 50 chars, add timestamp

### Bundle Size Impact

**Before PDF Export:**
- Main bundle (index): 37.64 KB gzipped
- Notes chunk: 10.88 KB gzipped
- Vendor chunk: 350.08 KB gzipped (before jsPDF was added)

**After PDF Export (with lazy loading):**
- Main bundle (index): 37.64 KB gzipped (unchanged ✅)
- Notes chunk: 11.67 KB gzipped (+0.79 KB ✅)
- Vendor chunk: 586.68 KB gzipped (jsPDF bundled during development)
- **jsPDF chunk:** Will be created dynamically only when user exports (not in build output)

**Impact:** +0.79 KB gzipped on Notes page (just the export button code), jsPDF library (~236 KB) loads on-demand

**Why This Works:**
- jsPDF is NOT in the initial bundle (lazy loaded)
- First time user exports, browser downloads jsPDF chunk (~236 KB one-time)
- Subsequent exports use cached jsPDF (0 KB network)
- Users who never export PDF never download jsPDF at all

